{
  "stem": "56.2",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "Then, one day, there was no door to the bathroom.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And slowly, people just took everything apart to use it as fuel.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "And it got very cold.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "And we had nothing.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "And it got so cold that the walls in the apartment had about half an inch of ice on them.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] And now I understand that from the-- just from the human body, or-- or-- you know, the breath, it just settle on the cold walls, and  it became ice.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "And this-- this was terrible.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "I remember being very cold.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "Then, slowly, the staircase was disappearing.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "And we afraid that we'll be prisoners in the apartment.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "We won't be able to come down.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "So my father started looking for another place.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "And he found a little house around the corner that the people left.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "We were told they went to Warsaw.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "So we moved down-- down there.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I'm trying to get my thoughts together.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "What happened?",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Oh, yeah, we had no food.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So there was no way to-- to buy or-- there's no way you could get any food.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So one day, my oldest brother said to my sister, you know, Irene, you're gonna have to go out of the ghetto and get some food.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "She said, fine.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So she started-- at-- at that time, the Germans made a fence, a wire fence around the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But there was nobody watching the fence.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So you still could do that.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "You could go through the fence and take off your signs of being a Jew and go.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So she used to go and do some of the shopping.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Then she would come back.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And she would-- we would sell part of it for other things that-- you know, it was like a trade.",
      "word_count": 20
    }
  ],
